Saurkraut Chocolate Cake
  --Taste of Home

1/2 c butter, softened
1 1/2 c sugar
1 c water
3 large eggs, room temp
3/4 c saurkraut, drained, squeezed dry, and chopped very fine
1 tsp vanilla
2 c ap flour
1/2 c cocoa
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt

In a bowl, cream the butter and sugar. Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with water. Stir in sauerkraut. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8" round baking pans. Bake at 350F for 35-40 min or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 min before removing to wire racks to cool completely. 

Frosting:
1 1/3 c butter, softened
4 oz unsweetened chocolate, melted
1 1/2 tsp vanilla
4 c confectioners' sugar
1/4 c whole milk

Beat butter, chocolate and vanilla in a bowl; add sugar and beat well. Add milk; beat until smooth and fluffy. Spread between layers and over top and sides of cake.


Notes: might be best to process kraut in food processor, otherwise will affect texture.
